Prosternum (
Fig. 47
): Prosternal lobe large, with apical margin distinctly incised medially; prosternal process sharply tricuspidate, sides obviously, arcuately expanded; disk deeply impressed, with lateral corners distinctly protruding ventrad. Apex of last abdominal ventrite distinctly emarginate.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 67
).

Distribution
