; 
Thailand
: Chiang Mai, Kanchanaburi, Loei, Mae Hong Son, Nan, Tak; 
Vietnam
.

Prosternum (
Fig. 49
): Prosternal lobe large, with apical margin arcuately emarginate; prosternal process with subparallel sides, disk impressed, lateral corners protruding ventrad. Basal abdominal ventrite without tubercles; apex of last abdominal ventrite slightly emarginate.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 69
).

Variability . Pronotal sides in basal third are sometimes divergent. Elytral pubescence in paratypes from the locality “Ban Saluei” is present also on humeral part (
Fig. 23
).

Etymology . The name is derived from the prefix semi - (Latin, partially, incompletely, somewhat) and caducus (Latin, subject to shedding), to indicate the variability in the extent of elytral pubescence (
Figs. 22–23
).
